Ionic introduction：

Ionic is a powerful HTML5 application development platform that makes it easy to build mobile applications
that are close to the native experience using Web technologies such as HTML, CSS, and Javascript.
Ionic focuses on the look and feel, as well as interacting with the UI of your application, 
and is particularly well suited for HTML5 mobile application development based on the Hybird model.
－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－
Features:
1. Run fast
2. Lightweight framework
3. Support Angularjs features, MVC, code easy to maintain
4. Build applications through SASS, provide a lot of UI components to help develop
5. Focus on native
6. Powerful command-line tools
7. Based on the angular syntax is easy to learn
－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－
Command-line installation:
1. First you need to install Node.js
2. Install from the command line:
   Window & Linux:  $ Npm install -g cordova ionic
   Mac:    Sudo npm install -g cordova ionic
Tip: IOS needs to be installed in Mac OS X. and Xcode environments.

3. If you have installed the above environment, you can run the following command to update the version:
    Npm update -g cordova ionic
               Or
   Sudo npm update -g cordova ionic
－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－   
Ionic Lab is the desktop development environment,if you do not like to use 
the command line operation,Ionic Lab will meet your needs.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Xamarin Introduction:
 Xamarin can be cross-platform development, including IOS, Android, WP and Mac App.
 Xamarin Studio is a C # language development environment, also includes its own UI generator,
 the perfect support for Visual Studio.
